9,808]},"species":"gyarados","gen":"generation-i","leg":false,"myth":false,"baby":false,"eggs":["water2","dragon"],"flavor":[{"version":"platinum","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a GYARADOS will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"They say that during past strife, GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake."},{"version":"red","text":"Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage."},{"version":"blue","text":"Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage."},{"version":"yellow","text":"Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times."},{"version":"gold","text":"They say that during past wars, GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake."},{"version":"silver","text":"Once it appears, it goes on a ram\u00ad page. It remains enraged until it demolishes every\u00ad thing around it."},{"version":"crystal","text":"It appears when\u00ad ever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through."},{"version":"ruby","text":"When MAGIKARP evolves into GYARADOS, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this POK\u00e9MON\u2019s wildly violent nature."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"Once GYARADOS goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn\u2019t calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this POK\u00e9MON\u2019s rampages lasting a whole month."},{"version":"emerald","text":"It is an extremely vicious and violent POK\u00e9MON. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames."},{"version":"firered","text":"It has an extremely aggressive nature. The HYPER BEAM it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage."},{"version":"diamond","text":"Once it appears, its rage never settles until it has razed the fields and mountains around it."},{"version":"pearl","text":"In ancient literature, there is a record of a GYARADOS that razed a village when violence flared."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it."},{"version":"black","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"white","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"black-2","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"white-2","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"x","text":"In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared."},{"version":"y","text":"Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s wildly violent nature."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Once Gyarados goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn\u2019t calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s rampages lasting a whole month."},{"version":"sun","text":"A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind."},{"version":"moon","text":"There are people who swear that any place Gyarados appears is fated for destruction."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"It fires hyper beams in all directions, burning the surrounding area to ash. There are some regions where it\u2019s called \u201cthe deity of destruction.\u201d"},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"The energy from evolution stimulated its brain cells strongly, causing it to become very ferocious."},{"version":"lets-go-pikachu","text":"Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times."},{"version":"lets-go-eevee","text":"Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times."},{"version":"sword","text":"It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets."},{"version":"shield","text":"Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm."},{"version":"legends-arceus","text":"I suspect this Pok\u00e9mon to be the true identity of a dragon written of in ancient texts, which claimed that it razed an entire village with white-hot beams from its maw."}],"evo":{"name":"magikarp","level":0,"min_level":null,"trigger":null,"item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":null,"turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[{"name":"gyarados","level":1,"min_level":20,"trigger":"level-up","item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":"","turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[]}]},"sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/130.png","shiny":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/shiny/130.png","capture":45,"happiness":70,"growth":"slow","gender":4,"hatch":5,"ev":{"attack":2},"forms":[{"id":10041,"name":"gyarados-mega","sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/10041.png"}]}